Tuumatehnoloogia seminari eesmärgiks on luua platform temaatiliseks diskussiooniks ning anda osalejate nii  ülevaade kui ka  tutvustus kaasaegsetest tuumatehnoloogiatest ning nende rakendustest. Sealhulgas käsitletletakse tuumareaktorieid ning nende kasutust energia tootmises ja kiirguse meditsiinilisi rakendusi. Tutvustatakse radioaktiivsete jäätmete liike ja käsitlemist, tutvustatakse kiirgus- ja tuumaohutuse tagamise põhimõtteid. Käsitletakse tuumatehnoloogiate laiemaid sotsiaalmajanduslikke mõjusid inimestele ja keskkonnale. Loengute käigus süvenetakse erinevatesse reaktoritehnoloogiatesse, uuritakse kiirguse mõju materjalidele ja inimestele, käsitletakse tuumajäätmete käitlemiset. Samas vaadeldakse ka olulisi tegureid nagu inimfaktor tuumatehnoloogias, tuumaohutus ning ühiskondlikud ja sotsiaalsed mõjud. Loengud viiakse läbi oma valdkonna erialaekspertide poolt.

The aim of the "Seminar on nuclear technologies" is to create a platform for thematic discussion and to give participants an overview and introduction of modern nuclear technologies and their applications. For example, these include nuclear reactors and their use in energy production, and medical applications of radiation. But not only, we also include the types and management of radioactive waste, the principles of nuclear and radiation safety, the wider socio-economic impacts of nuclear technologies. During the lectures, various reactor technologies, the effects of radiation on materials and people, and nuclear waste management will be introduced. However, important factors such as the human factor in nuclear technology, nuclear safety and societal and social impacts are also considered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce different nuclear technologies and their applications, to provide information on the types of radioactive waste and their treatment, and to introduce the principles of ensuring radiation and nuclear safety.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  - Knows the uses and operating principles of nuclear technology. - Can describe the types and methods of radioactive waste and respective waste management methods. - Understands the principles of radiation and nuclear safety. - Can analyze and evaluate the impact of nuclear technology in the context of Estonian economy, people and environment.
